I’ve isolated three concrete verifier issues from the local source and logs: the route discovery was misclassifying the real Optimism route because the OpStack route advertises the same ERC20 getter, the token scan skipped likely fork-resident stables entirely, and the raw `1e15` token threshold made 6-decimal profits impossible to record. I’m rewriting `src/FlawVerifier.sol` around those fixes while preserving the same vulnerable call pattern.
